thread.title: Jack Sock Advances in Sweden
thread.title_full: Jack Sock Advances in Sweden - The New York Times

author: The Associated Press
title: Jack Sock Advances in Sweden
text:
Jack Sock and Marcos Baghdatis advanced to the second round of the Stockholm Open with hard-fought wins, but Jarkko Nieminen ended his singles career with a loss to Nicolas Almagro.
The seventh-seeded Sock hit 11 aces to beat Pablo Carreno Busta, 6-3, 6-7 (1), 6-3. Baghdatis, the 2009 champion, was taken to a first-set tiebreaker before beating Sam Querrey, 7-6 (2), 6-1. Almagro beat Nieminen, who was making his 16th straight appearance in Stockholm, 3-6, 7-6 (6), 6-4.
■ Gaël Monfils made a winning return from a seven-week injury layoff, rallying to beat Thomaz Bellucci, 6-7 (5), 6-3, 6-4, in the first round of the Erste Bank Open in Vienna.
